																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>To most people, the <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-scj/fulltext/2017/12000/exploring_the_standing_barbell_overhead_press.7.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">barbell shoulder press</a> is regarded as one of the big three movements. If added onto the big three, this would make it the big four. While its not officially on the list, we think its worth including.</p>



<p>Variations of the barbell shoulder press include the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-bench-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell bench press</a> and push press. Like the shoulder press, each of these offers several functional benefits when programmed correctly.</p>



<p>Building bigger and stronger shoulders requires exercises that target all three deltoid heads. Our barbell shoulder exercises use a range of functional movements. Alongside this, they work the full chest and shoulder complexes.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In the article below, we discuss the nine best barbell shoulder workouts for bigger and stronger delts. If youre looking for well-rounded shoulders, look no further than the exercises below.&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-group box-grey is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size"><strong>Best Barbell Shoulder Exercises</strong></p>



<p>Each compound exercise below is designed to work the full shoulder complex. Performing them correctly can improve functional movement and overhead performance. These are the best exercises:</p>



<ol>
<li><a href="#Military-Press">Military Press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Arnold-Press">Arnold Press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Barbell-Shrug">Barbell Shrug.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Barbell-Front-Raise">Barbell Front Raise.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Barbell-Upright-Row">Barbell Upright Row.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Barbell-Bench-Press">Barbell Bench Press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Incline-Barbell-Bench-Press">Incline Barbell Bench Press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Barbell-Push-Press">Barbell Push Press.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Seated-Barbell-Shoulder-Press">Seated Barbell Shoulder Press.&nbsp;</a></li>
</ol>



<p>Make sure that you follow the correct technique cues for targeted muscle activation. The exercises below can be added to any of your workouts depending on your exercise goals. Our barbell shoulder workout applies the fundamental scientific principles to give you the best exercises to follow.&nbsp;</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">9 Barbell Shoulder Workouts For Bigger And Stronger Deltoids</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Military-Press">Military Press</h3>



<p>You can do several workouts to keep your shoulders in great shape. However, the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-military-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Military Press</a> is perfect for <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7706677/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">strengthening your muscles around</a> the posterior deltoid, trapezius, and core. It indirectly targets other shoulder muscles, like the triceps. These isolation exercises are suitable for intermediate or advanced weightlifters. (Isolation exercises use single joint movements using one muscle group).</p>



<p>You only need a barbell to get started with a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-arm-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell arm workout</a> after a few warm-ups. A Seated Dumbbell Press suits people with low back pain.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Barbell Military Press" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/963306554?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Military Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin the Military Press by warming up, involving two sets of 30/30 light push presses, meaning you rest warm for 30 seconds and rest for 30 seconds. Proceed with two sets within two minutes continuously and pause again.</li>



<li>Place the barbell in a squat rack. Take the bar out of the rack support and lift the weight straight up with the extended arms. Move two steps backward to get enough space, your feet shoulder-width apart, to lift the bar.</li>



<li>While standing with your feet together, squeeze your core muscles and glutes hard for stability to press from, and maintain that position for a while.</li>



<li>With your elbows pointing forward, use your chin to hold your bar level. Such an angle helps you involve the side deltoids and the front to lift heavier and stay in control.</li>



<li>Lower the bar and let your head move back slightly so that your forehead does not knock on the bar on the way down. You can now relax once the weight is down.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Before attempting this lateral raise workout, ensure you&#8217;re targeting the appropriate muscles to minimize the risk of injury.</li>



<li>Protect your lumbar spine from overextending by maintaining a neutral hip ( hip and pubic joints in the same plane) during the exercise. If maintaining a neutral hip becomes challenging, leave the exercise and work on your form first.</li>



<li>Ensure you keep your glutes tight because weak and loose glutes put you at risk of injury.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">45</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">58</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">34</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">812</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">23</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1215+</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">35</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">36 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Military Press</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Arnold-Press">Arnold Press</h3>



<p>Named after Arnold Schwarzenegger, this barbell exercise<strong> </strong>strengthens your shoulder&#8217;s medial deltoid muscles, including the posterior deltoid and rear delts. This workout suits bodybuilders or athletes who need shoulder stability. However, avoid this workout if you have a shoulder injury. You can do it while seated if you are experiencing lower back problems.</p>



<p>You can opt for these barbell exercises if you desire to experience prolonged muscle tension using a unique palm-turning motion when you light the weight. Use dumbbells to increase shoulder stability when performing the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-arnold-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Arnold press</a> workout.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Arnold Press" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/970347896?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arnold Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Sit on a flat bench and hold the two dumbbells of your desired weight from the rack while your palms face your body. This is the starting position.</li>



<li>Let your feet be shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Begin to create movements by raising the dumbbells while rotating the palms of your hands until they face upwards.</li>



<li>Persist in lifting the dumbbells and letting them extend above you, shoulder height, as you retain the straight arm position. Continue performing this movement as you breathe out, shoulders straight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause and lower these dumbbells to their former positions while rotating your palms for strong <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/arms-and-shoulders-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">arms and shoulders</a>.&nbsp;</li>



<li>As you lower down the dumbbells, ensure you rotate the left arm crosswise while the right arm is in an anti-clockwise manner.</li>



<li>Continue breathing as you rotate your arms.</li>



<li>Repeat this workout depending on your fitness level.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Include a good diet, rest, and warm-ups in your workout programs.</li>



<li>Select a proper weight that allows you to stay in command of the movements. You can lift heavier weights as your strength improves.</li>



<li>Never allow your head to move forward excessively.</li>



<li>If you sense any pain in your body, stop the exercise promptly.</li>



<li>Rest for at least a day before performing workouts to enable efficient recovery.</li>
</ul>



