<li>Allow your spine to stay in a neutral position as you remain in your standing position, your arms shoulder width apart.</li>



<li>Elevate the barbell to shoulder height. If unable, the load is too heavy.&nbsp;</li>



<li>In a shoulder-straight position, exhale and hold the contraction for a second.</li>



<li>Squeeze hard at the top and slowly lower the bar to the starting position.</li>



<li>Return to the original position as you breathe in.</li>



<li>Repeat the steps according to the desired reps; do not overtrain.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>You should use the correct weight when doing this exercise to prevent injuries and other casualties.</li>



<li>You can get a better trap (strength training exercise) by doing explosive movements and high reps.</li>



<li>Always pause at the end of the workout to promote mind-muscle connection.</li>



<li>Avoid jutting the head forward excessively when squeezing traps because it can trigger a neck injury.</li>



<li>Apply variations at a different angle to result in bigger traps.</li>
</ul>



