<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Barbell-Front-Raise">Barbell Front Raise</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-front-raise" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Barbell Front Raises</a> are the best shoulder workouts for any beginner or bodybuilder, as they stabilize muscles in the shoulders and neck. These <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/front-delt-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">front delt workouts</a> target shoulder muscles such as the lateral and anterior deltoid.</p>



<p>These barbell shoulder exercises can affect the trapezius muscles. You will also involve the abdomen in the workout as you contract your abs and perform <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-rear-delt-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">rear delt exercises</a>.</p>



<p>As you move during these upright row exercises, you increase the size of your anterior deltoids as you apply your speed, reps, and sets.</p>



<p>These barbell exercises engage the front lateral deltoid as you perform multiple pressing movements to strengthen the muscles. After all, you need a bigger front deltoid to enhance a wider-framed upper body. Consequently, a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-tricep-barbell-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell arm workout</a> enables one to lift heavier objects, like placing heavier objects on a shelf.</p>



