<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Barbell-Bench-Press">Barbell Bench Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-bench-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell bench press</a> is a foundational strength exercise that forms the backbone of many powerlifting routines. It uses a functional movement pattern that requires strength, coordination, and technique.</p>



<p>The primary movers are the three heads of the pectoralis major. The triceps brachii, anterior deltoids, and serratus anterior perform secondary roles.</p>



<p>It acts as a compound pressing exercise that works most of the upper-body musculature. Because of this, weve included it on our list.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Barbell Bench Press" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/963978466?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Barbell Bench Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand next to a flat bench with a suitable barbell. Make sure the barbell is loaded with the safety clips in place.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Lie on the bench with your back and head against the backrest. Bring your hands forward and grasp the bar with a double overhand grip (palms facing upward). Your arms should be shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Make sure that the barbell is in line with your upper chest.</li>



<li>Retract your shoulder blades and unrack the barbell.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and slowly lower the barbell towards your chest. Pause briefly as it reaches the bottom position.</li>



<li>Inhale and push back to the start under control.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your back firmly pressed against the backrest. This ensures targeted muscle activation.</li>



<li>Your feet should stay firmly on the floor throughout the movement. This is the correct bench press position.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



