</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Incline Barbell Bench Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up next to an adjustable bench. Adjust the backrest so it&#8217;s at a 4560 degree angle.</li>



<li>Lie on the bench with your back and head against the backrest. Bring your hands forward and grasp the barbell using a double overhand grip. Your arms should be shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and flex your elbows. Allow the bar to lower to your upper chest.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the bottom position. Inhale and push the barbell back to the starting position under control.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your chest up with your head facing forward. This ensures that your clavicular heads are the primary movers.</li>



<li>Set the bench angle at approximately 4560 degrees. This is the correct movement pattern.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



