<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Barbell-Push-Press">Barbell Push Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-push-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell push press</a> is a functional shoulder movement. It uses a small leg drive which adds a dynamic element to the normal pressing movement.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The primary movers are the anterior deltoids and the lateral deltoids. The secondary movers are the glutes, quadriceps, calves, and core musculature.</p>



<p>The <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Chris-Bishop-2/publication/319061549_Exercise_Technique_The_Push_Press/links/59db9f190f7e9b1460fbff34/Exercise-Technique-The-Push-Press.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">push press</a> develops strength, power, and full-body coordination. It&#8217;s a challenging full-body exercise that&#8217;s worth including in any pressing program.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Push-Press_Shoulders" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/986912063?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Barbell Push Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand in front of a suitable rack with the barbell at upper chest height.</li>



<li>Grasp the barbell using a double overhand grip. Your hands should be shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Bring your elbows forward, allowing the barbell to sit in the palms of your hands. Keep your elbows tucked into your sides throughout the movement.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Unrack the barbell and take a step back.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and perform a partial squat until your quads are parallel to the floor. Press the bar up and straighten your legs while driving your hips forward.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your chest up with your head facing forward throughout.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position. Inhale and lower the barbell down under control.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Press the bar once your quads come parallel to the floor as you straighten your legs. This is the correct movement pattern.</li>
</ul>



<p>The press and leg drive should form one fluid movement. Ensure they work together on every repetition.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



